, England, United Kingdom","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom","Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, England","Great Mereley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nowell","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Yorkshire and Lancashire): variant of   Noel  ,   Knowles  , or   Newell  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Nowels","meanings":["Altered form of   Nowell   or   Noel  , with the addition of excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Noel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Pierre, Normand, Antoine, Jacques, Alphonse, Leonce, Lucien, Marcel, Damien, Emile, Francois.","French and Walloon (<b>Noël</b>); English: from the Old French personal name <i>Noël</i>, Middle English <i>Noel</i>, from Old French <i>no(u)el</i> ‘Christmas’ (from Latin <i>natalis (dies)</i> ‘birthday’), used for someone born during the Christmas period. Alternatively, a nickname for someone who had some special connection with the Christmas season, such as owing the particular feudal duty of providing a yule-log to the lord of the manor, or having given a memorable performance as the Lord of Misrule. This surname is also found in the Flemish part of Belgium. Compare   Christmas   and   Newell  .","English: sometimes a post-medieval variant of <b>Knowle</b> and   Knoll   (see   Knowles  ). The loss of /k/ before /n/ is known in everyday speech by the 17th century and may have been earlier."]}]},{"name":"Anne","type":"FIRST","meanings":["A name corrpted from Hannah, q.v. It is also found several times in a male name. From Ann, Anne, we have as nicknames Nan and Nancy"],"variants":[{"name":"Nancy","meanings":["Of uncertain origin. From the 18th century it is clearly used as a pet form of   Ann   (  see  Nan  ), but it may originally have been a similar formation deriving from the common medieval given name   Annis  , a vernacular form of   Agnes .  Nowadays it is an independent name, and was especially popular in America in the 1930s, 40s, and 50s."]},{"name":"Nan","meanings":["Originally a pet form of   Ann   (for the initial <i>N-</i>,  compare  Ned  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Nowell was born in Lancashire, England, United Kingdom. She married Sir William Fleming I of Wath, Croston and Mawdesley before 1420. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died after 1461."},"et":{"–after 1461":"–pärast 1461","1390–1451":"1390–1451","–1483":"–1483","1420–1451":"1420–1451","1429–1470":"1429–1470","–1461":"–1461","March 1429":"märts 1429","before 1420":"enne 1420","Aft 1451":"pärast 1451","1451":"1451","1461":"1461","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","1420":"1420","about 1420":"umbes 1420","after 1461":"pärast 1461","after 1451":"pärast 1451","1429":"1429","Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Croston, Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Croston, Lancashire, England":"Croston, Lancashire, England","Great Mereley, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Lancashire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–after 1461":"–1461 jälkeen","1390–1451":"1390–1451","–1483":"–1483","1420–1451":"1420–1451","1429–1470":"1429–1470","–1461":"–1461","March 1429":"maaliskuu 1429","before 1420":"ennen vuotta 1420","Aft 1451":"1451 jälkeen","1451":"1451","1461":"1461","1483":"1483","1470":"1470","1390":"1390","1420":"1420","about 1420":"noin 1420","after 1461":"1461 jälkeen","after 1451":"1451 jälkeen","1429":"1429","Croston, Lancashire, England, United Kingdom":"Croston, Lancashire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Wath upon Dearne, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Croston, Lancashire, England